President Obama delivered remarks at the Christmas in Washington event held at the National Building Museum. He thanked the host, Ellen DeGeneres, and the performers for their participation. The event benefited the Children's National Medical Center. The President highlighted the message of peace and salvation brought by the birth of Jesus Christ and emphasized the importance of loving and caring for one another. He expressed prayers for the troops, those who are unemployed, and those facing hardships during the holiday season. President Obama encouraged people to remember the true meaning of Christmas by practicing charity, compassion, and goodwill towards others. He concluded by extending holiday greetings and blessings to everyone.